    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-06-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-06-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="309"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d309">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.51/1344.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Chargé d’Affaires of the Dominican
                            Republic</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                        State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 50.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dominican Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 9, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                    receipt of your very kind note dated the 1st instant and referring to that of
                    May 26 last from the Legation. I am informed thereby that President Wilson has
                    designated Mr. Charles M. Johnston as Financial Expert, in accordance with the
                    said note of May 26.</p>
                <p>With regard to the interpretation put by the Department on the phrase “to
                    conserve and put into execution the original agreement of increasing the
                    revenues,” it is proper to declare that the Dominican Government’s understanding
                    is that the financial expert may devise and put into operation additional
                    measures for increasing the revenues, but that those measures can not be put
                    into execution without the sanction of the Dominican authorities in cases where
                    that sanction is required by our Constitution and laws.</p>
                <p>I renew [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">I. A. Cernuda</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
